    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
    </p>
    
    <p>
    <ul>
        <li>
        <p>
            The circumference is the distance round a circle.
        </p>
        </li>
        <li>
        <p>
            When you divide the circumference by the diameter of any circular object, the number you get is 
            approximately <m>3.142</m> correct to three decimal places.
            <me>
            \frac{\text{Circumference}}{\text{diameter}} = 3.142
            </me>            
        </p>
        <p>
            Circumference <m>= 3.14 \times\text {diameter}</m>
        </p>
        </li>
        <li>
        <p>
            The number <m>3.142</m> is called <m>\textbf {pi}</m> and is represented by the symbol <m>\pi</m>. As a fraction, <m>\pi = \frac {22}{7}</m>.
            Therefore, circumference <m> = \pi d</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            or
        </p>
        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow>\pi= \amp \frac{C}{D}=\amp \frac{C}{2r}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        </li>
        <li>
        <p>
            Two radii are equal to the diameter. Hence <m>d = 2r</m>            
        </p>
        <p>
            Circumference 
            <md>
            <mrow>= \amp  \pi \times d</mrow>
            <mrow>= \amp \pi \times 2r</mrow>
            <mrow>= \amp 2\pi r </mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        </li>
    </ul>
    </p>

    <figure>
        <caption>Perimeter of different plane figures.</caption>
